{
  "doc_id": "45094",
  "text": "Recent studies have reported the modification of lipid levels in prognosis of different types of cancers. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] For instance, reduction of cholesterol in oral cancers is alarming for the progression of cancerous lesions. [CITATION_3] Opposite results regarding the association between lipid levels and cancer progression seem to be due to the type of tumor and also by pathophysiological role of lipids related to cancer progression.",
